President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Carolyn "Carrie" Hessler Radelet as the Director of the Peace Corps. Hessler Radelet has been the Deputy Director of the Peace Corps since 2010 and has played a crucial role in recruiting and training volunteers for the organization. She has previous experience working for John Snow, Inc. and the U.S. Agency for International Development. Hessler Radelet has also served as a Peace Corps Volunteer in Western Samoa and holds a B.A. from Boston University and an M.S. from Harvard School of Public Health.